Material Information Summary (Drilling Results Announcement):

  • Exploration Highlights:

  • Danvers Copper Project:

    • Maiden drilling (May 2025) confirmed historic resource with intercepts including 175m @ 2.5% Cu, 90m @ 4% Cu, and 105m @ 2.25% Cu.
    • Summer campaign (August 2025) extended mineralization strike length to >400m (up from initial ~150m).
    • Visible sulphides observed in all 4 completed holes (assays pending September 2025).
    • Notable intercept: DAN25012 (100m step-out) – 59m of visible sulphides from 56m, including >10m of ~5% bornite + 3% chalcocite.
    • Target for further drilling: Expand to >800m strike and test new outcrop zone 4.5km SW of Danvers.

  • Upcoming Catalysts:

  • Assay results (Danvers + Hulk Project) expected September 2025.

  • Drone MT survey results (Danvers lease) due late August 2025.

  • Operational Update:

  • Diamond drilling resumed at Hulk Project with new contractor; initial assays also expected September.

  • Caution: Visual estimates only; assays required to confirm grades.

Key Highlights (Clinical Trial Results - ACCENT Study)

  • Progression-Free Survival (PFS): 7.6 months, a 2-month improvement over chemotherapy alone (benchmark: 5.5 months in MPACT study).
  • Durability: Mean Days on Trial (DOT) of 202 days vs. 117 days for chemotherapy alone.
  • Efficacy:
  • Objective Response Rate (ORR): 31% (vs. 23% for chemotherapy).
  • Disease Control Rate (DCR): 73% (vs. 50% in MPACT).
  • Includes 1 Complete Response (CR) and 1 pathological CR.
  • Tolerability: Adverse event profile similar to standard chemotherapy (gemcitabine/Abraxane), with negligible added burden.

Upcoming Catalysts

  • Further ACCENT trial updates: 2H 2025 (patient data) and mature data expected Q1 2026.
  • Phase 2b/3 pivotal trial planned for initiation in 2H 2026.
  • AMPLICITY trial (US/Australia, FOLFIRINOX combo): First patient dosing imminent.

Regulatory Status

  • FDA Fast Track and Orphan Drug Designation granted for pancreatic cancer.
